radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix measures up to 9-mm in diameter, fluid-filled with mucosal hyperenhancement and periappendiceal stranding. No free fluid or definite evidence of perforation noted. All other abdominal organs (liver, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, pancreas, gallbladder) and pelvic structures are unremarkable. Duplicated renal collecting system noted bilaterally. No suspicious lytic or blastic lesions or fracture.
